  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "display_name": "Jordan",
    "long_instructions": "<br/>\r\n\r\n1. **Look** at your user profile to understand their needs and challenges.\r\n\r\n2. **Drag** each checklist box onto the part of the app where it applies.\r\n\r\n3. **Mark** the box to show how well the design works for your user:\r\n\r\n    * If it works well, color it green or add a check.\r\n\t![](https://images.code.org/84cea069e797c25d32211afbf5f5ad57-green.png)\r\n    \r\n    * If it doesn't work well, color it red or add an X.\r\n    ![](https://images.code.org/17499d23a47a868f4420655827aa5604-red.png)\r\n\r\n4. **Point** an arrow to the part of the app that works well or needs improvement.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**User Profile:**\r\n\r\n\r\n- **Name**: Jordan\r\n- **Age**: 16\r\n- Uses a phone daily to listen to music and podcasts.\r\n- Switches quickly between playlists and dislikes hidden menus.\r\n- Gets frustrated when apps are slow, cluttered, or hard to navigate.",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Jordan listens to music all day on a mobile phone. Help check if the app is fast, simple, and easy to use while switching between playlists.",
